[01:11] <dmknopp> Hello all, I would like to loop thru all the HLL objects alive in Parrot. It seems to me that the AddrRegistry PMC would be a good place to ask for information on all those objects.
[01:11] <dmknopp> Is this recommended to do in a HLL using PIR?
[01:12] <chromatic> They're not stored in AddrRegistry.
[01:13] <dmknopp> the mem addresses are stored right?
[01:13] <chromatic> No.
[01:13] <dmknopp> key : mem addr value: ref count
[01:13] <dmknopp> hmm... ok
[01:13] <chromatic> AddrRegistry is only a member of the root set used to anchor otherwise-unanchored PMCs for GC.
[01:13] <chromatic> PMCs returned to embedding programs, for example.
[01:14] <dmknopp> drat. back to square 1
[01:14] <dmknopp> ok, thanks.
[01:14] <chromatic> If an HLL such as Cardinal wanted to track all objects created in that language, it would need something like Ruby's ObjectSpace.
[01:15] <dmknopp> :-) thats what I was hoping to implement
[01:15] <dmknopp> I was hoping AddrReg was a hash of all live objects which I could then tarverse and inspect
[01:16] <chromatic> We don't have anything like that now, unless you write C code to scan all PMC pools.
[01:16] <dmknopp> Do you have an suggestions on adding an ObjectSpace like functionality?
[01:16] <dmknopp> ok
[01:16] <chromatic> For Parrot in general or a specific HLL?
[01:16] <dmknopp> scan all PMC pools, I will have to look into that
[01:17] <dmknopp> im thinking for HLL and Cardinal specificly
[01:17] <dmknopp> but i guess other languages might need this type of thing as well
[01:17] <chromatic> Then you add something to the MOP for that language to cache all created objects with weak references.
[01:18] <dmknopp> Are we talking the P6 protoobject
[01:18] <chromatic> Or the Cardinal equivalent.
[01:18] <dmknopp> or maybe the find_method :vtable
[01:19] <dmknopp> ok, yeah right now Cardinal uses the P6 protoobject
[01:20] <chromatic> Add an initializer to Cardinal's Object which registers the object in ObjectSpace, and add a finalizer which unregisters it.
[01:21] <dmknopp> Right now, I believe in Cardinal, that all objects that are created go thru the CardinalObject.new. This would be a good place maybe to add the initializing code.
[01:21] <chromatic> That's what I'd do.
[01:22] <dmknopp> When you say register with the object in ObjectSpace, Do you mean create a hash of WeakRef PMCs , can I do that? Or does ObjectSpace mean some thing more specific I havent learned about?
[01:22] <dmknopp> err "register the object in ObjectSpacee"
[01:22] <chromatic> It's just a hash with a mark vtable entry which doesn't do anything.
[01:23] <chromatic> You'd have to write it, but it's easy to write.
[01:32] <dmknopp> ok thanks
